    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nRegular expressions in vim are far more powerful than Lua pattern.\r\n`vim.regex()`, however, has few methods. It can only know the overall match position, and to use submatches, you need to use matchlist from vim.fn, for example. This would be bad for performance because it involves type conversion between vim and lua.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWe need `regex:match_list()`, like `matchlist()`.",
