            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "A specific use case is pattern matching to rgb functions, which I do in [my plugin](https://github.com/uga-rosa/ccc.nvim). lua pattern cannot express this.\r\nAnd this is how vim.fn.matchstrpos() and regex:match_str() benchmark. In my environment, the difference is about 3x (0.594063 vs 0.17935), I don't know which the pre-compilation by vim.regex() or the type conversion has a bigger impact, but is this not enough?\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal time = os.clock()\r\nfor _ = 1, 100000 do\r\n  vim.fn.matchstrpos(\r\n    \"rgb(50 50 50 / 0.5)\",\r\n    \"\\\\Vrgba\\\\?(\\\\s\\\\*\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\s\\\\+\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\s\\\\+\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\s\\\\*\\\\%(/\\\\s\\\\*\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)%\\\\?\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\)\\\\?\\\\s\\\\*)\"\r\n  )\r\nend\r\nvim.pretty_print(os.clock() - time)\r\n---> 0.594063\r\n\r\ntime = os.clock()\r\nlocal re = vim.regex(\r\n  \"\\\\Vrgba\\\\?(\\\\s\\\\*\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\s\\\\+\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\s\\\\+\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\s\\\\*\\\\%(/\\\\s\\\\*\\\\(\\\\[+-]\\\\?\\\\%(\\\\d\\\\+.\\\\?\\\\d\\\\*\\\\|.\\\\d\\\\+\\\\)%\\\\?\\\\|none\\\\)\\\\)\\\\?\\\\s\\\\*)\"\r\n)\r\nfor _ = 1, 100000 do\r\n  re:match_str(\"rgb(50 50 50 / 0.5)\")\r\nend\r\nvim.pretty_print(os.clock() - time)\r\n---> 0.17935\r\n```\r\n\r\nEven if use match() instead of matchstrpos(), A large difference was observed (0.486866 vs 0.176187).",
